17 possession proof that he or she has completed a National Association of State Boating
18 Law Administrators approved boater education course or equivalency examination from
19 another state.
20 (2) No person shall rent, lease, or let for hire any vessel ten horsepower or more to any
21 person under 18 years of age. No person shall operate a vessel that has been rented,
22 leased, or let for hire unless such person is 18 years of age or older and has completed a
23 rental education course approved by the department. A person 18 years of age or older
24 may rent, lease, or let for hire a vessel ten horsepower or more if such person has
25 completed a rental education course approved by the department. No person may rent,
26 lease, or let for hire a vessel ten horsepower or more to a person 18 years of age or older
27 unless such person has completed a rental education course approved by the department
28 and, if one or more additional persons 18 years or age or older will be present on such
29 vessel, at least one additional person has completed such course.
30 (3) Rental education courses provided pursuant to paragraph (2) of this subsection must
31 be approved by the department and must result in the issuance of a rental education
32 certificate upon successful completion of the course. Rental education certificates shall
33 be effective for six months after the date of issuance and shall be valid anywhere in this
34 state. Boat liveries shall use course materials approved by the department. At a
35 minimum, a course must consist of a ten-minute operation familiarization video followed
36 by a renter orientation checklist. Such video must address the following topics in order
37 to be approved:
38 (A) Operator responsibility, ethics, courtesy, and good judgment on the water;
39 (B) Safety equipment;
40 (C) Navigation rules;
41 (D) Aids to navigation, and buoys and other waterway markers; and
42 (E) Proper identification.
